    "The expected value along a policy π is denoted as E π.V π (s) = E π R (t)|s (85) Q π (s, a) = E π R (t)|s, a(86)The optimal value and quality function correspondingly follow the optimal policy:V (s) = max π V π (s), (87)Q(s, a) = max π Q π (s).",
    "(88)The approaches can be subdivided into model-based and model-free.",
    "Model-based methods incorporate a model of the environment.",
    "In the most general sense, a probabilistic environment, this entitles the probability distribution of the next state P(s t+1 |s t, a t) and of the next reward R(r t+1 |s t+1, s t, a t).",
    "The model of the environment can be cheaply sampled to improve the policy π with model-free reinforcement learning techniques [647][648][649][650] discussed in the sequel (Appendices C.1 and C.2)."
